  <folder>
    <_title>Other Maemo Weather</_title>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Introduction</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_intro"/>
      <_para>Welcome to Other Maemo Weather.</_para>
      <_para>
        Other Maemo Weather (OMWeather) is a weather applet for Nokia Internet
	Tablets. It can be used to:
      </_para>
      <list>
        <_listitem>
          Check the detailed weather forecast for up to 10 days
        </_listitem>
        <_listitem>
          Update weather information automatically from the Internet (Data
	  provided by weather.com)
        </_listitem>
        <_listitem>
          Configure the nearest weather station automatically using GPS
        </_listitem>
        <_listitem>
          Easily select a custom weather station from the sorted drop down menu
        </_listitem>
        <_listitem>
          See the sunrise and sunset times for selected weather stations
        </_listitem>
        <_listitem>
          See the current phase of the moon
        </_listitem>
        <_listitem>
          Select between different icon sizes, icon sets, colors and view modes
        </_listitem>
        <_listitem>
          Marvel at the eye candy with the new transparency option
        </_listitem>
       </list>
      <_para>
        Use the <ref refid="help_omweather_" refdoc="index"/> to access the
        various sections of this help document.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Getting Started</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_getstarted"/>
      <_para>
        To activate OMWeather select <display_text>Home</display_text> 
        <display_text>Select applets...</display_text>
        <display_text>OMWeather</display_text>.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        First, select the position of a OMWeather applet in home view.
	You can change applet's position simply touching it and dragging
	it where you want it. The applet's appearance can be changed from the
	<display_text>Tool</display_text> icon in OMWeather's weather window or
	by selecting <display_text>Home</display_text>
	<display_text>Applet settings</display_text>
        <display_text>OMWeather settings</display_text>.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        OMWeather will use the tablet's home city selection as a default location
        for weather data. The location can be changed from the
	<display_text>Stations</display_text> tab in OMWeather's settings window.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	More information on changing the applet's appearance and adding, renaming and
	deleting locations can be found on the 
	<ref refid="help_omweather_settings" refdoc="Settings"/> page.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Settings</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_settings"/>
      <_para>
        The <display_text>Settings</display_text> dialog (accessible from
        the desktop applet or home view's applet settings menu) provides
        access to the configurable options that control how OMWeather
        looks and operates.  In addition to the tabs to switch between screens, 
        there are also four buttons: the left arrow will take you to the weather 
        view, the [OK] button saves any changes you made to the settings, the
        question mark [?] opens the help window, and the [x] button closes the 
        settings window.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        The <display_text>Stations</display_text> tab lists all of the locations 
        for which OMWeather will retrieve weather data when an update is manually
        or automatically triggered.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        The <display_text>Visuals</display_text> tab is used to configure 
        settings that control the visual appearance of OMWeather.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        The <display_text>Display</display_text> tab is used to configure 
        settings that control the number of visible items on-screen, the icon 
        size, and other OMWeather parameters.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        The <display_text>Units</display_text> tab is used to select the display
        units used for display of temperature, distance, wind speed and barometric
        pressure.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        The <display_text>Update</display_text> tab is used to configure 
        the interval between weather data updates.  This tab will also indicate
        the time until the next update. 
      </_para>
      <_para>
	The <display_text>Sensor</display_text> tab is used control the
	usage of the Nokia's internal temperature sensor.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Settings. Stations tab</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_settings_stations"/>
	<_para>
        The left pane allows you to rename or remove
	stations from the list. The <display_text>up</display_text> and
	<display_text>down</display_text> arrows allow you to change
	the display order of the locations.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        The <display_text>add</display_text> pane allows you to add new
        weather stations, which will then appear in the left view.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        The <display_text>Enable GPS</display_text> check box is used to
	enable automatic weather station selection when GPS is enabled. 
	This option is only functional under OS2008.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Settings. Visuals tab</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_settings_visuals"/>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Layout:</display_text> defines how icons are arranged
        on the home screen.
      </_para>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Icon set:</display_text> defines which icon set is used.
	More icon sets may be installed via the Application Manager (if you have the
    Maemo Extras repository configured) or by downloading icon sets directly from
    OMWeather's Maemo garage page (http://omweather.garage.maemo.org/).
      </_para>
      <_para>
        The <display_text>UI Theme Override</display_text> selection allows you to 
        override the theme settings on your tablet and use settings specified within 
        OMWeather, instead.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	The <display_text>Transparency:</display_text> selection operates differently according
    to which Operating System is installed on your tablet: Under OS2006-OS2007, it will show a
	background image behind the weather icons. Under OS2008, this option allows you to select
    the percentage of transparency.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Font:</display_text> defines the font and font size used
	by the applet.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Font color:</display_text> defines applet's font color.
	Selecting the color button will open the <display_text>Pick a Color</display_text> 
    dialog where you may choose a font color.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Background color:</display_text> setting defines the background
	color used for icons.  Under OS2006-OS2007, the background color can not be
	selected if the transparency option is selected.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Type of click:</display_text> setting defines how full forecast and
	settings windows can be activated from home applet. 
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Settings. Display tab</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_settings_display"/>
      <_para>
        <display_text>Visible items:</display_text> defines how many icons
        will be shown on the tablet's home screen.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Icon size:</display_text> defines icon size.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	The <display_text>Show only current weather on first icon</display_text>
	selection will show current weather on first icon and forecast for the
	rest of the day is shown on the next icon.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	The <display_text>Swap hi/low temperature</display_text> selection will
	change the manner in which the forecast low and high temperatures are displayed.
	If selected, applet will show high temperature first.	
      </_para>
      <_para>
	The <display_text>Show wind</display_text> selection will display wind
	speed and direction on the applet.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Show station name:</display_text> this selection will
	control whether station names are shown on the applet.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Show arrows:</display_text> this selection controls
	whether the arrows (used to change the displayed weather station) are 
    shown on the applet.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Settings. Units tab</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_settings_units"/>
      <_para>
        The <display_text>Units</display_text> tab is used to select units
	for temperature, distance, wind speed and barometric pressure.  Necessary
	units can be selected by clicking on the corresponding button.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Settings. Update tab</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_settings_update"/>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Automatically update data when connecting to the Internet:
	</display_text> this selection controls the automatic weather data update when
	an Internet connection is established.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	<display_text>Switch to the next station after:</display_text> this drop down
	menu controls the amount of time a specific weather station's data is displayed
    before changing to the next weather station.
      </_para>
      <_para>
	Valid time for current weather and update interval may be also selected from
	the corresponding drop down menu. 
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Settings. Sensor tab</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_settings_sensor"/>
      <_para>
	When the <display_text>Use device temperature sensor</display_text> check
	box is enabled, the applet will display the temperature indicated by the 
    built-in temperature sensor on the Nokia tablet.  Temperature can be shown 
    after station name, or on a new icon.
	The sensor read interval may be set from 1 to 30 minutes.
      </_para>
    </topic>
    <topic>
      <_topictitle>Using Desktop Applet</_topictitle>
      <context contextUID="help_omweather_usingdesktopapplet"/>
      <_para>
        Touching the icon for a specific day brings up a window 
    displaying the current weather or detailed forecast for that day.
	On the <display_text>Now</display_text> tab you can see current
	weather at that station, and phase of the moon.  <display_text>Day</display_text>
	tabs will show weather forecast	and sunrise/sunset times for 
	selected days. 
      </_para>
      <_para>
	The <display_text>Tool</display_text> button will open the OMWeather
	settings dialog:  The <display_text>Refresh</display_text> button will
	update weather data, the <display_text>Question mark</display_text>
	will open OMWeather help text, and the <display_text>X</display_text> button
	closes weather dialog and returns to the applet's main display.
      </_para>
    </topic>
